{
  "page": "House Volmark",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\">House Volmark of Volmark</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Volmark.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"House Volmark.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/25/House_Volmark.svg/250px-House_Volmark.svg.png\" width=\"250\" height=\"275\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/25/House_Volmark.svg/375px-House_Volmark.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/25/House_Volmark.svg/500px-House_Volmark.svg.png 2x\" /></a><div></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Coat of arms</th><td>\nA black leviathan on a grey sea<br />(<i>Cendrée, a leviathan sable</i>)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Seat</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Volmark\" title=\"Volmark\">Volmark</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Head</th><td>\nLord <a href=\"/index.php/Maron_Volmark\" title=\"Maron Volmark\">Maron Volmark</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Regions</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Volmark\" title=\"Lord of Volmark\">Lord of Volmark</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Greenshield\" title=\"Lord of Greenshield\">Lord of Greenshield</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Overlord</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Harlaw\" title=\"House Harlaw\">House Harlaw</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>House Volmark of Volmark</b> is a noble house from the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a>. Their seat of <a href=\"/index.php/Volmark\" title=\"Volmark\">Volmark</a> is on the island of <a href=\"/index.php/Harlaw\" title=\"Harlaw\">Harlaw</a>, and they are sworn to the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Harlaw\" title=\"House Harlaw\">house of the same name</a>. They have large holdings on the island and have a decorated history.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>They blazon their arms with a black <a href=\"/index.php/Leviathan\" title=\"Leviathan\">leviathan</a> on a grey sea.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Their words are not known.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#House_Volmark_at_the_end_of_the_third_century\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">House Volmark at the end of the third century</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Historical_Members\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Historical Members</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Volmark&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>After the death of King <a href=\"/index.php/Harren_Hoare\" title=\"Harren Hoare\">Harren Hoare</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Burning_of_Harrenhal\" title=\"Burning of Harrenhal\">burning of Harrenhal</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Qhorin_Volmark\" title=\"Qhorin Volmark\">Qhorin Volmark</a> claimed the title of <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"King of the Iron Islands\">King of the Iron Islands</a>, as his grandmother was the younger sister of King <a href=\"/index.php/Harwyn_Hoare\" title=\"Harwyn Hoare\">Harwyn Hardhand</a>. Qhorin was slain by King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Invasion_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"Invasion of the Iron Islands\">invasion of the Iron Islands</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/2_AC\" title=\"2 AC\">2&#160;AC</a>, however.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Goren_Greyjoy\" title=\"Goren Greyjoy\">Goren Greyjoy</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"Lord of the Iron Islands\">Lord of the Iron Islands</a>, defeated a conspiracy to crown Qhorin's son in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_33_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">33&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_greyjoys_of_pyke.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_greyjoys_of_pyke.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord Volmark was put to the sword by <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westermen</a> during Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Johanna_Lannister\" title=\"Johanna Lannister\">Johanna Lannister</a>'s invasion of the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/134_AC\" title=\"134 AC\">134&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Volmark&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Volmark&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>When the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsmoot\" title=\"Kingsmoot\">kingsmoot</a> is summoned, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Rodrik_Harlaw\" title=\"Rodrik Harlaw\">Rodrik Harlaw</a> calls his bannermen in <a href=\"/index.php/Asha_Greyjoy\" title=\"Asha Greyjoy\">Asha Greyjoy</a>'s name. Among others, the Volmarks gather at <a href=\"/index.php/Ten_Towers\" title=\"Ten Towers\">Ten Towers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> While standing ashore on <a href=\"/index.php/Old_Wyk\" title=\"Old Wyk\">Old Wyk</a> a Volmark greets <a href=\"/index.php/Victarion_Greyjoy\" title=\"Victarion Greyjoy\">Victarion Greyjoy</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Tarle_the_Thrice-Drowned\" title=\"Tarle the Thrice-Drowned\">Tarle the Thrice-Drowned</a> claims that Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Maron_Volmark\" title=\"Maron Volmark\">Maron Volmark</a> has the best claim on the <a href=\"/index.php/Seastone_Chair\" title=\"Seastone Chair\">Seastone Chair</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Aeron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Aeron Greyjoy\">Aeron Greyjoy</a> spots the banners of House Volmark among those gathered for the kingsmoot on Old Wyk. During the kingsmoot, however, all the lords and captains are free to choose their candidate, and Maron supports Victarion.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the <a href=\"/index.php/Taking_of_the_Shields\" title=\"Taking of the Shields\">taking of the Shields</a> by the <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a>, King <a href=\"/index.php/Euron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Euron Greyjoy\">Euron Greyjoy</a> names Maron as Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Greenshield\" title=\"Greenshield\">Greenshield</a>. Victarion interprets it as a way to reinforce Euron's prestige by gaining the support of the young lord, who descends from <a href=\"/index.php/Harren_Hoare\" title=\"Harren Hoare\">Black Harren</a>'s line through his mother.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"House_Volmark_at_the_end_of_the_third_century\">House Volmark at the end of the third century</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Volmark&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: House Volmark at the end of the third century\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The known Volmarks during the timespan of the events described in <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i> are:\n</p>\n<ul><li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Maron_Volmark\" title=\"Maron Volmark\">Maron Volmark</a>, Lord of Volmark and of Greenshield. A young boy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffcappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwdappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Historical_Members\">Historical Members</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Volmark&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Historical Members\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Qhorin_Volmark\" title=\"Qhorin Volmark\">Qhorin Volmark</a>, a claimant after the death of <a href=\"/index.php/Harren_Hoare\" title=\"Harren Hoare\">Harren the Black</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabreign_of_the_dragon_-_the_wars_of_king_aegon_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n<ul><li>His son, who was defeated by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Goren_Greyjoy\" title=\"Goren Greyjoy\">Goren Greyjoy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_greyjoys_of_pyke.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_greyjoys_of_pyke.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></li>\n<li>Lord Volmark, put to the sword by <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westermen</a> during Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Johanna_Lannister\" title=\"Johanna Lannister\">Johanna Lannister</a>'s invasion of the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/134_AC\" title=\"134 AC\">134&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Volmark&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-edits